        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 6. Halecium beanii (Johnston, 1838). (A–D) After material from South Africa; (E–F) after material from New Zealand. (A) Two internodes (scale bar: 0.2 mm); (B) female gonotheca in oblique view (scale bar: 0.2 mm); (C) cross-section of female gonothecae in about the middle of its height, note polygonal outline (same scale bar as B); (D) three male gonothecae, note variability (same scale bar as B); (E) two internodes (same scale bar as A); (F) female gonotheca (same scale bar as B)." ;
